Vice President Kamala Harris spoke at an event in Washington, D.C., where she praised small-business owners and entrepreneurs for their innovation and contribution to the economy. She highlighted the Biden administration's focus on creating jobs, rebuilding American manufacturing, and investing in infrastructure. Harris also emphasized the importance of expanding access to capital for small businesses and announced a $125 million investment in 43 small-business accelerators. These accelerators will provide support and guidance to entrepreneurs, particularly in underserved communities, to help them succeed in the clean energy economy. Harris concluded by expressing her belief that investing in small businesses creates opportunities and prosperity for everyone.